dations are! Sick abusers like her will still get away with it because they play ball and fool those set with the job of monitoring them. &#10;Victoria Climbie was neither home educated, nor 'unknown' and it is an insult to her memory to try excusing the professional who failed her by pretending that she was either! Read the Serious Case Review and then tell me how home education had anything to do with it. &#10;As for declining 'registration' being &quot;pathetic and paranoid&quot;. Registration isn't what is being suggested, it's LICENSING. Registration would just mean saying &quot;we're home educating&quot; once and you're done, no home inspections, no proving your innocence on an annual basis, no plans of study, no testing. The DCSF choose to keep calling what they're after 'registration' to generate precisely your reaction, but that's because they're fundamentally dishonest scum. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1177" language="en" documentId="947" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="firebird2110" date="06 November 2009 6:00pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6747131" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="9" thumbsDown="0" origId="947" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="445"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="446" end="714"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="715" end="1177"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator2" isPersuasive="false" labelDetailed="P27" isGold="false" comment="there are some references given here about which no sufficient background knowledge is available.. hard for me to decide.." annotationBatchName="batch2-690documents" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator3" 